#: ../../source/comparison.md:29
msgid "A couple of clarifications:"
msgstr "几点说明："

#: ../../source/comparison.md:31
msgid ""
"**Gymnasium and PettingZoo are interfaces, not simulators.** They "
"standardise how an agent talks to an environment; IR-SIM can sit *behind* "
"such an interface to provide the dynamics."
msgstr ""
"**Gymnasium 和 PettingZoo 是接口，而非仿真器。** 它们规范了智能体与环境之间的交互方式；IR-SIM "
"可以位于这类接口*之下*来提供动力学。"

#: ../../source/comparison.md:32
msgid ""
"IR-SIM deliberately trades physical fidelity for **minimal setup and speed "
"of iteration** — it models kinematics and collisions, not contact forces or "
"photorealism."
msgstr "IR-SIM 有意以物理保真度换取**最少的配置与快速的迭代**——它建模运动学与碰撞，而非接触力或拟真效果。"

#: ../../source/comparison.md:34
msgid "In short"
msgstr "一言以蔽之"

#: ../../source/comparison.md:36
msgid ""
"If you want the fastest path from an idea to a running navigation, control, "
"or multi-agent RL experiment — and you don't need 3D physics or photorealism"
" — IR-SIM is built for exactly that. When fidelity matters more than "
"iteration speed, pair it with (or graduate to) one of the heavier simulators"
" above."
msgstr ""
"如果你想以最快的速度把一个想法变成可运行的导航、控制或多智能体强化学习实验——并且不需要 3D 物理或拟真效果——那么 IR-SIM "
"正是为此而生。当保真度比迭代速度更重要时，可以将它与上述更重的仿真器配合使用（或迁移过去）。"

